title: NFL Week 6 point spreads, over/under: Packers, Patriots biggest favorites
text:
The Green Bay Packers and New England Patriots are the biggest favorites in Week 6 of the NFL season.
The Packers are a 10.5-favorite at home against the San Diego Chargers. The Patriots are favored by nine points on the road against the Indianapolis Colts in a rematch of last year's Deflategate game.
The Buffalo Bills continue to be a three-point underdog against the Cincinnati Bengals. The game opened as a pick 'em.
Below are the odds for NFL games next week courtesy of America's Line.
